  67,27,"Then when they see the torment drawing near, the faces of the disbelievers will become gloomy, and it will be said ˹to them˺, “This is what you claimed would never come.”"
  67,28,"Say, ˹O Prophet,˺ “Consider this: whether God causes me and those with me to die or shows us mercy, who will save the disbelievers from a painful punishment?”"
  67,29,"Say, “He is the Most Compassionate—in Him ˹alone˺ we believe, and in Him ˹alone˺ we trust. You will soon know who is clearly astray.”"
  67,30,"Say, “Consider this: if your water were to sink ˹into the earth˺, then who ˹else˺ could bring you flowing water?”"
